OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMauritius oil spill: MV    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FWakashio ship captain      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsentenced                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The captain and first officer of a ship
OL,6, that ran aground on a coral reef in    
OL,7, Mauritius have each been sentenced to  
OL,8, 20 months in prison.                   
OL,10,FAbout 1,000 tonnes of fuel oil from the
OL,11,FJapanese-owned MV Wakashio leaked into 
OL,12,Fthe ocean in July 2020, causing        
OL,13,FMauritius' worst ecological disaster.  
OL,15,FThe magistrate said she hoped that the 
OL,16,Fsentence would "serve as a lesson" for 
OL,17,Fthe men, and other potential offenders.
OL,19,FBoth had pleaded guilty to endangering 
OL,20,Fsafe navigation.                       
